news.title: Enhanced power of LPA will help expedite projects: Credai Coimbatore
news.para: "As the Local Planning Authority is now empowered to give approvals to plans up to 2,500 square metres, we can finish the process within three months,” said Gugan Elango, president of Credai, Coimbatore.

news.title: Lucknow development body to start digital mapping to check illegal construction
news.para: On Wednesday, scientists of the Remote Sensing Application Centre held a meeting with LDA authorities and gave a presentation of the satellite survey and mapping activities carried out by them in Ghaziabad district.

news.title: Jaipur: 65 old buildings in Walled City yet to be demolished
news.para: The focus on diilapidated buildings comes a day after the wall of an old house collapsed near Jorawar Singh Gate. Though no one was injured, it could have led to a big mishap. Civil defence and police took two hours to clean the area.

news.title: Delhi: Construction, demolition waste plant fined for flouting pollution norms
news.para: ​Officials of the DPCC said several deficiencies, including unavailability of "wheel washing facility, water sprinklers", were found at the Rise Eleven Delhi Waste Management Company site during an inspection on July 2.

news.title: Rajasthan: Verification of 26,000 construction workers complete
news.para: Labour secretary Neeraj K Pawan informed that under the state-level registration campaign, 1726 construction sites were visited by several registration teams and 46,689 construction workers were given information about the welfare schemes of the labour department.

news.title: Goa: Flat owners facing sale deed hurdles pin hopes on cooperative societies bill
news.para: In many instances, buyers have been unable to register a sale deed for a flat/shop they purchased some years ago either because the builder is not alive or he is unwilling to initiate the process. The recently passed Goa Cooperative Societies (Amendment) Bill, however, is set to improve the fate of such property owners.

news.title: Noida: Owners of plots lying idle get a year's time to finish construction
news.para: On August 31, 2020, the Industrial Area Development Act was amended and the authority was given the power to cancel land deeds for plots that were allotted but left vacant for years.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Nearly 4,000 acres 'locked' for township since 2009 may go back to owners
news.para: “Wave group and Suncity were given licences to develop the township, under which there was a plan to construct 2 lakh dwelling units. While Wave group was supposed to acquire 4,400 acres of land, Suncity was to acquire 4,300 acres,” Shivpuri said.

news.title: Mumbai: BDD chawls residents to pay just Rs 1,000 as stamp duty
news.para: ​​The new housing units will be free but the government will charge Rs 1,000 as stamp duty and agreement cost per house from eligible residents, it said.

news.title: GIC Housing to seek shareholders' nod for raising upto Rs 2,500 crore next month
news.para: "Shareholders' approval is being sought in the aforesaid 31st AGM of the company for fundraising by way of issue of redeemable non-convertible debentures/bonds on a private placement basis up to aggregate the limit of Rs 2,500 crore," GIC Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: KKR to sell industrial properties for $2.2 billion to Oxford Properties Group
news.para: The portfolio comprises 149 buildings across 12 major industrial markets including Dallas, Chicago and Houston. Oxford and its portfolio companies manage about C$70 billion ($55.5 billion) of assets, according to its website.

news.title: Ludhiana Improvement Trust's last bid to get buyer for Rani Jhansi Road property
news.para: The initial reserve price of Rs 197 crore made this building unattractive to the bidders for long. But even when the price was lowered to about Rs 157 crore, no one showed up to buy it.

news.title: Global prime residential index witnesses annual increase of 8.2%: Report
news.para: The report released on Wednesday said premium micro-markets of the city remained unchanged on a QoQ basis in Q2 to record an average price of Rs 33,572 per square feet.

news.title: Gurugram: Ambiguity over cost may delay piped water in some societies
news.para: To get a connection, housing societies need to pay around Rs 3-4 lakh to GMDA as the basic fee. Apart from this amount, cost will also have to be incurred for laying pipelines and related infrastructure from the society till the master line.

news.title: Thane civic body acts on unauthorised constructions in Majiwada-Manpada ward
news.para: In Wagbhil, the action was taken on the fifth floor of the stilt plus five-storey building. Similar actions were taken in Koliwada and Kasarwadavli too.
